<div class="container" id="process">
  <section class="process">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="eyebrow">// how it works</div>
      <h2>Four steps to a codebase you actually own</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="process-track">
      <div class="process-step">
        <div class="step-dot"></div>
        <div class="step-label">01 Intake</div>
        <h3>Share your repo</h3>
        <p>Send us a link and describe what's broken. We respond within 2 hours with an honest assessment.</p>
        <span class="time">~2 hours</span>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step">
        <div class="step-dot"></div>
        <div class="step-label">02 Diagnose</div>
        <h3>Deep code audit</h3>
        <p>A senior engineer reads every file, maps the architecture, and documents every issue with a prioritized fix plan.</p>
        <span class="time">~24 hours</span>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step">
        <div class="step-dot"></div>
        <div class="step-label">03 Operate</div>
        <h3>Fix, refactor, test</h3>
        <p>We fix critical bugs first, then restructure, then add tests and docs. You get daily progress updates.</p>
        <span class="time">~5-8 days</span>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step">
        <div class="step-dot"></div>
        <div class="step-label">04 Handoff</div>
        <h3>You own it</h3>
        <p>Walkthrough call, full documentation, and 2 weeks of support. Clean, tested code that your team can maintain.</p>
        <span class="time">~1hr + 2 weeks</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

